description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Innovation &amp; Intelligent Automaton team, we are recruiting talented intelligent automation experts to scale and accelerate the deployment of automation in the Trust and wider health and care community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to work with highly complex automation projects and will be part of a team creating world-class automation solutions across clinical and corporate areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team-wide Business Support function provides focused admin support within the Innovation and Intelligent Automation Team, providing support for a number of corporate functions and across the wider teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business Support will provide a comprehensive support service within the Trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There will be an expectation for the post holder to be highly motivated, flexible and multi-skilled with excellent organisational skills and the ability to take minutes/notes at meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will have high standard word processing skills and computer literacy. They will be required to maintain an up-to-date knowledge of Information Technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will need to meet deadlines, collate data and maintain standards relating to administrative processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;They will need to be able to work within a team effectively, working across office sites and shared work streams where appropriate, whilst maintaining confidentiality as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
